### Abbreviations

* DP → Dynamic Programming
* SW → Smith–Waterman
* MT → Multi-threaded
* SA → Suffix Array
* MPI → Message Passing Interface

Why Renegene-GI?
* Renegene do not rely on heuristic alogrithm but rather used Smith waterman-DP.
* Renegene-GI considers multiple sequence alignments (MSA) and repeat regions, which are often omitted by other aligners to increase it mapping qulaity.
* The above point directly helps in reporting more variants such as SNPs and INDELs. 

We made use of 16 sam metrics and 8 VCF matrics for analysis, as mentioned below


| No. | SAM Metrics                | Description                        |                                
| --- | -------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |  
| 1   |Singleton Rate              | Only one mate mapped               |   
| 2   | Discordant Pairs           | Abnormal pair orientation          | 
| 3   | Error Rate                 | Mismatch/indel rate                |
| 4   | MQ0                        | Rate Reads with MQ = 0             |  
| 5   | Clipped Bases Rate         | Soft/hard clipped bases            |
| 6   | Secondary Alignments       | Multi-mapped reads                 |
| 7   | Supplementary Alignments   | Split alignments                   |
| 8   | Insert Size SD             | Variation in insert size           |
| 9   | Minimum Depth              | Threshold Minimum coverage cutoff  |
| 10  | Insert Size                | Mean Fragment length               |
| 11  | Overall Mapping Rate       | Fraction of reads aligned          |
| 12  | Properly Paired Rate       | Correctly paired reads             |
| 13  | Avg Mapping Quality (MPQ)  | Confidence of mapping              |            
| 14  | Mean Depth of Coverage     | Average coverage                   |
| 15  | Breadth of Coverage        | Genome covered                     |
| 16  | Coverage Uniformity        | Evenness of coverage               |
 
| No. | VCF Metrics                | Description                                 | 
| --- | -------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |  
| 1   | Total Records (Variants)   | Total number of variant calls in VCF        |   
| 2   | SNPs                       | Number of single nucleotide polymorphisms   | 
| 3   | Indels                     | Insertions and deletions                    |
| 4   | MNPs                       | Multi-nucleotide polymorphisms              |  
| 5   | Multiallelic Sites         | Sites with >2 alleles                       |
| 6   | Transitions (Ts)           | A to G, C to T substitutions                |
| 7   | Transversions (Tv)         | Purine ↔ pyrimidine substitutions           |
| 8   | Ts/Tv Ratio                | Ratio of transitions to transversions       |

